libcpan-meta-requirements-perl (2.140-2) unstable; urgency=medium

  [ Salvatore Bonaccorso ]
  * debian/control: Use HTTPS transport protocol for Vcs-Git URI

  [ gregor herrmann ]
  * debian/copyright: change Copyright-Format 1.0 URL to HTTPS.

  [ Salvatore Bonaccorso ]
  * Update Vcs-* headers for switch to salsa.debian.org

  [ gregor herrmann ]
  * debian/watch: use uscan version 4.

  [ Debian Janitor ]
  * Bump debhelper from old 9 to 12.
  * Set debhelper-compat version in Build-Depends.
  * Set upstream metadata fields: Bug-Submit.
  * Remove obsolete fields Contact, Name from debian/upstream/metadata
    (already present in machine-readable debian/copyright).
  * Remove constraints unnecessary since stretch:
    + Build-Depends-Indep: Drop versioned constraint on libversion-perl and
      perl.
    + libcpan-meta-requirements-perl: Drop versioned constraint on
      libversion-perl and perl in Depends.
    + libcpan-meta-requirements-perl: Drop versioned constraint on
      libcpan-meta-perl in Replaces.
    + libcpan-meta-requirements-perl: Drop versioned constraint on
      libcpan-meta-perl in Breaks.

